+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KTy6WYikS7XaD2qCBrafSk","type":"tool_result","content":"# Phase 5: Retry with Backoff\n\nAdd automatic retry functionality so that failed tasks can be re-attempted with increasing delays.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- There should be a way to mark a processing task as completed or failed.\n- When a task fails and has retries remaining, it is automatically re-added to the queue with a delay.\n- The delay follows exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (e.g., 1s, 2s, 4s, ...).\n- The default maximum number of retries is 3, but this should be configurable per task.\n- The base backoff delay defaults to 1000ms but should be configurable per task.\n- The task should track how many times it has been attempted.\n- Retried tasks keep their original queue and priority.\n- If all retries are exhausted, the task remains in a failed state.\n===\n# Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue\n\nAdd a dead letter queue (DLQ) to capture tasks that have permanently failed after exhausting all retries.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- When a task has no more retries left, it is automatically moved to a dead letter queue associated with its original queue.\n- There should be a way to view all dead-lettered tasks for a given queue.\n- Dead-lettered tasks should retain their error information and a count of how many times they failed.\n- It should be possible to move a dead-lettered task back to its original queue for a fresh round of retries.\n- There should be a way to clear all dead-lettered tasks for a queue.\n- Each named queue has its own independent dead letter queue.\n===\n# Phase 7: Task Dependencies\n\nAdd the ability for tasks to declare dependencies on other tasks, so they only become available once their prerequisites are done.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- When adding a task, you can specify a list of task IDs that must complete before this task becomes available.\n- A task with unresolved dependencies is blocked and will not be returned when retrieving.\n- When a dependency completes, the system should check whether any blocked tasks are now unblocked.\n- Circular dependencies (direct or indirect) must be detected and rejected at task-creation time.\n- Depending on a non-existent task should cause an error.\n- A failed dependency does NOT automatically fail its dependents -- they remain blocked.\n- There should be a way to inspect a task's dependency status.\n===\n# Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n\nAdd per-queue limits on how many tasks can be processed at the same time.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Each queue can have a maximum concurrency setting that limits how many tasks can be in a processing state simultaneously.\n- If the concurrency limit is reached, retrieving a task returns `null` even if pending tasks are available.\n- Completing or failing a task frees up a concurrency slot.\n- By default, queues have no concurrency limit (unlimited).\n- There should be a way to set and query the concurrency limit and current active count for a queue.\n- Concurrency interacts correctly with priority ordering -- the highest-priority available task is still chosen, subject to the concurrency limit.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9fdf3cb0-a31b-443c-80cc-10b087bdbae1","uuid":"c89b8f23-f48e-4be7-ba15-cf4f59ca290b","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"# Phase 5: Retry with Backoff\n\nAdd automatic retry functionality so that failed tasks can be re-attempted with increasing delays.\n\n## Requirements\n\n- There should be a way to mark a processing task as completed or failed.\n- When a task fails and has retries remaining, it is automatically re-added to the queue with a delay.\n- The delay follows exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)` (e.g., 1s, 2s, 4s, ...).\n- The default maximum number of retries is 3, but this should be configurable per task.\n- The base backoff delay defaults to 1000ms but should be configurable per task.\n- The task should track how many times